:1px solid #f1f5f9;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;color:#94a3b8;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:4px;\">EDUCATION &mdash; CYCLE 2, DAY 1 (REVISIT)</div>\n  <div style=\"font-size:17px;font-weight:700;color:#1e293b;margin-bottom:12px;\">Forward P/E vs Trailing P/E &mdash; Why It Matters on Earnings Week</div>\n  <p style=\"margin:0 0 10px;font-size:13px;color:#374151;line-height:1.6;\">MSFT and META report July 29 &mdash; same day as CAPR AdCom. Before the prints, analysts publish forward P/E estimates. Here&rsquo;s the live mechanic:</p>\n  <div style=\"background:#fff;border:1px solid #e2e8f0;border-radius:8px;padding:14px;margin-bottom:12px;\">\n    <table style=\"border-collapse:collapse;width:100%;font-size:12px;\">\n      <tr style=\"border-bottom:2px solid #e2e8f0;\">\n        <th style=\"padding:6px 8px;text-align:left;color:#94a3b8;font-size:10px;text-transform:uppercase;\">Metric</th>\n        <th style=\"padding:6px 8px;text-align:left;color:#94a3b8;font-size:10px;text-transform:uppercase;\">Definition</th>\n        <th style=\"padding:6px 8px;text-align:left;color:#94a3b8;font-size:10px;text-transform:uppercase;\">When to use</th>\n      </tr>\n      <tr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #f1f5f9;\">\n        <td style=\"padding:8px 8px;font-weight:700;color:#1e293b;\">Trailing P/E</td>\n        <td style=\"padding:8px 8px;color:#374151;\">Price / last 12mo actual EPS</td>\n        <td style=\"padding:8px 8px;color:#64748b;\">Backward-looking. Useful for mature businesses.</td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td style=\"padding:8px 8px;font-weight:700;color:#1e293b;\">Forward P/E</td>\n        <td style=\"padding:8px 8px;color:#374151;\">Price / next 12mo estimated EPS</td>\n        <td style=\"padding:8px 8px;color:#64748b;\">What the market trades on. MSFT/META at 28&ndash;32&times; forward P/E.</td>\n      </tr>\n    </table>\n  </div>\n  <div style=\"padding:10px 14px;background:#dbeafe;border-radius:6px;border-left:3px solid #3b82f6;margin-bottom:10px;\">\n    <strong style=\"color:#1d4ed8;font-size:12px;\">Live example Jul 29:</strong>\n    <p style=\"margin:6px 0 0;font-size:12px;color:#1e3a8a;line-height:1.5;\">If MSFT beats and raises guidance, EPS estimate rises. At 30&times; forward P/E, EPS $14 &rarr; $14.50 justifies stock at $435 vs prior $420. That&rsquo;s a re-rating, not speculation &mdash; pure math. TSLA yesterday: missed EPS 38%, estimate revised down, stock dropped in AH. Same mechanism in reverse.</p>\n  </div>\n  <div style=\"padding:10px 14px;background:#f0fdf4;border-radius:6px;border-left:3px solid #059669;\">\n    <span style=\"font-size:12px;color:#166534;font-weight:600;\">&#127891; Cycle 2 begins.</span><span style=\"font-size:12px;color:#166534;\"> All 30 concepts completed Jul 21. Concepts now revisit with live examples from your actual trades. Forward P/E is #1 because it&rsquo;s the mechanism behind every earnings move this week.</span>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<!-- WHAT TO DO TOMORROW -->\n<div style=\"padding:16px 24px;border-bottom:1px solid #f1f5f9;background:#fffbeb;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;color:#94a3b8;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:10px;\">WHAT TO DO TOMORROW &mdash; FRIDAY JULY 25</div>\n  <table style=\"border-collapse:collapse;width:100%;font-size:13px;\">\n    <tr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #fde68a;\"><td style=\"padding:8px 0;vertical-align:top;width:24px;font-size:16px;\">1.</td><td style=\"padding:8px 8px;color:#374151;line-height:1.5;\"><strong>Read FDA briefing docs when posted.</strong> Search \"CAPR Capricor FDA briefing documents July 2026.\" PDFs on FDA.gov. Read FDA reviewer section on LVEF and PUL endpoints first.</td></tr>\n    <tr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #fde68a;\"><td style=\"padding:8px 0;vertical-align:top;font-size:16px;\">2.</td><td style=\"padding:8px 8px;color:#374151;line-height:1.5;\"><strong>Decision:</strong> Supportive docs &rarr; HOLD. 